d sharing of material  such as music  movies  games  and applications  for which the copyright holder has not given rights  Enterprise Technical Architecture This policy addresses two topics  facilities telecommunications infrastructure and telecommunications  FOIA  Freedom of Information Act FERPA Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act Computer Lab Rules Rules for computer labs  Mission Critical Policy  This document outlines computer systems designated as mission critical  Multimedia Support This document outlines the support provided for multimedia classrooms  Password Policy  This document outlines the VMI Password Policy  Password Descriptions  This document outlines the restrictions which control the creation of passwords used for various accounts at VMI including the domain  Post View  and Colleague accounts  Security Awareness  The Commonwealth of Virginia has developed an Information Technology Security Standard upon which VMI Security Awareness Policy is based  Software Copyright Policy  This document outlines the software copyright policy  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 